:::summary
Philosophy — from the Greek *philosophia*, meaning "love of wisdom" — is the disciplined study of fundamental questions about reality, knowledge, morality, and existence. Born in ancient Greece, it has shaped every intellectual tradition in the Western world and remains one of the most powerful tools for clear thinking. Latter-day Saints are encouraged to seek wisdom from "the best books" (D&C 88:118), and philosophy provides the rigorous habits of mind that make serious inquiry possible.
:::

